  "texts": [
    "However, all other mNb6 humanized variants show a binding compromised to varying degrees.",
    "The least affected variant is the one from the AbNatiV exhaustive sampling, with a K D of 15 ± 2 nM, followed by the two AbNatiV variants that also contain mutations at buried sites.",
    "The most affected variant is the one from the frequency and structure-based humanization, which did not yield any binding signal in the assay (Fig. 5d and Supplementary Fig.",
    "In terms of stability, the enhanced sampling variants show a slight decrease of apparent melting temperature over that of the WT, but an unaffected or marginally improved temperature of unfolding onset.",
    "Conversely, the enhanced sampling variant with mutations at buried positions and the frequency and structure-based variant had decreased thermal stability, while both exhaustive sampling variants had increased thermal stability (Fig. 5h, j)."
  ]
}